mpus Housing will be assigned to students living in residence halls without private cooking facilities. Students living in UIC apartment style residence halls or off campus students can also purchase a Traditional Meal Plan. Purchases can be made in person at the ID Center. Traditional Meal Plans are non refundable and may only be paid for by charging the purchase to a USFS Student Account. See www.uic.edu/depts/dining/traditional.shtml for more details.       Note about Student Account Billing   By requesting funds be billed to your student account‚ you acknowledge financial responsibility for the additional charges to your student account. We reserve the right to refuse to provide services billed to a student account when that student account is past due at the time of the request UIC does not mail billing statements to enrolled students. You must check your E-Bill online for these additional charges. These charges are due when billed. Any billing may take up to one month to appear on your student account. Visit below for more information about billing and payment options. There is a $100 minimum and $1000 maximum for student account billing.    www.usfsco.uillinois.edu         Refunds   A refund from your UIC Dragon Dollar$ account or Traditional Meal Plan is given only when separation from the university occurs. You must request a refund through the Meal Plan Office‚ and must accompany the request with proof of separation. Traditional Meal Plans are refundable based on a weekly prorating schedule. If you are a student‚ Dragon Dollar$ refunds are transferred to your student account to cover any outstanding balances. The remaining credit balance‚ if any‚ will be transferred via direct deposit to the account on file with the University of Illinois. Other patrons‚ including faculty and staff‚ may be refunded through University check.       Notification of Loss or Theft   If your ID card is lost or stolen‚ you must notify the ID Center immediately to limit liability. A replacement ID card can be obtained in either of the ID Centers‚ Room 1790 SSB or Room 241 SCW during office hours. You will be charged a replacement fee. Once your ID card has been replaced‚ your old ID card will be deactivated. Once you have replaced a card or reported it missing‚ the old card cannot be reactivated.       Account Inactivity   If an account with a positive balance or unused meals has sustained no activity for a period of 12 months or more‚ the account will be determined to be inactive until one of the following occurs:   The account holder requests that the account be returned to active status.  The account has been inactive for 24 months‚ at which time‚ remaining funds are turned over to unclaimed property of the University.        Obtaining account balances and histories   Dragon Dollar$ debit account balances are available at the registers of the UIC Dining Services and Convenience Store facilities. When you access an account‚ balances are displayed on paper or electronically. Balances are also available at dragoncenter.uic.edu. Dragon Dollar$ transaction history may also be obtained over the phone from the Meal Plan Office or at dragoncenter.uic.edu. For security reasons‚ account balance information is disclosed only to the account holder with proper identification.    dragoncenter.uic.edu         Account Holder Liability   As an account holder‚ you are liable for all transactions made on your ID card‚ except for any unauthorized use after you report your card missing. Error Resolution Procedures and Account Holders´ Rights In case of errors or questions about your Dragon Dollar$ or Meal Plans account‚ e-mail idcenter@uic.edu or call the ID Center and   Give your name‚ telephone number‚ and University ID number (UIN).  Describe the error or the transaction you are unsure about‚ and explain as clearly as you can why you believe it is an error or why you need more information.  Give the dollar amount of the suspected error.   You may be required to send your complaint or question in writing within 10 business days. Failure to respond may result in the complaint or question not being resolved.  You will be notified of the results of our investigation within 5 business days after we hear from you. Any errors will be promptly corrected.  MasterCard is a registered trademark of MasterCard International Incorporated. VISA is a registered trademark of Visa in the United States and other countries. Discover is a registered trademark of NOVUS Credit Services Inc. American Express is a registered trademark of American Express Company  *Terms and Conditions may be subject to change          Dragon Dollar$ and Flames Fare    Back to main content           Using Dragon Dollar$ and Flames Fare    Purchase Locations & Fees    Terms & Conditions    Meal Plans    Add Dragon Dollar$ and Flames Fare Online                  UIC Logo        ID Center       Contact   idcenter@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 